2 possible etymolgies:

(1) from Irvine/Irvin/Irving, ultimately from the town of Irvine near Glasgow.
(2) from the Old English 'ir' (=wild boar) and 'wyn' (=friend). See also Wynn.

Ultimately, (1) is the most likey for Scottish and Irish (esp. Ulster ancestry), (2) for English ancestry. Note that (1) and (2) can also be spelt 'Erwin' and that (2) only, even but rarely, as 'Urwin'.